Definition: large shrub of tropical Africa and Asia having large palmate leaves and spiny capsules containing seeds that are the source of castor oil and ricin
Example: widely naturalized throughout the tropics
Synonyms: castor_bean_plant, palma_christi, palma_christ, Ricinus_communis, shrub, genus_Ricinus, m, large, of, tropical, Africa, and, Asia, having, palmate, leaves, spiny, capsules, containing, seeds, that, are, the, source, castor, oil, ricin, widely, naturalized, throughout, tropics
Category: noun.plant
